.TH "ufshcd_query_descriptor_retry" 9 "ufshcd_query_descriptor_retry" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ufshcd_query_descriptor_retry \- API function for sending descriptor requests
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ufshcd_query_descriptor_retry
.BI "(struct ufs_hba *hba "  ","
.BI "enum query_opcode opcode "  ","
.BI "enum desc_idn idn "  ","
.BI "u8 index "  ","
.BI "u8 selector "  ","
.BI "u8 *desc_buf "  ","
.BI "int *buf_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hba" 12
per-adapter instance
.IP "opcode" 12
attribute opcode
.IP "idn" 12
attribute idn to access
.IP "index" 12
index field
.IP "selector" 12
selector field
.IP "desc_buf" 12
the buffer that contains the descriptor
.IP "buf_len" 12
length parameter passed to the device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 for success, non-zero in case of failure.
The buf_len parameter will contain, on return, the length parameter
received on the response.
